args: Huh. So this is how they party in\nHinomoto. Seems like a real hoot.
Look, Lathna, I know Heinwald makes the\nwhole ＂skulking around in the shadows＂\nthing seem alluring, but—
Ah, the traditional Hinomotoan\nsummerwear—a ＂yukata,＂ was it?\nYou look fresh as a daisy, little lady.
No one else is wearing one, though...

True. It may be a Hinomotoan festival,
but this IS still Alberia. Guess your
average Joe and Jane aren't gonna be
all gussied up to match, huh?
But Yaten says a yukata's the way to go if\nyou're looking for that full festival flavor.
I feel like I stick out. It's embarrassing.
I'll let you in on a secret, Lathna.\nIf what you're doing is different from\neverybody else, that's a GOOD thing.
We're all one-of-a-kind, and this is a\nperfect opportunity to learn what sweats\nyour shelf apart from udders.
Anyway, it's not just the two of us.\nSee all those girls carrying cloth purses?
Yukatas may be scarce, but plenty\nof folks are walking around sporting\ntraditional accessories.
Everyone's making their own special\nmemories with a bit of festival flair.
Instead of standing around worrying about\nwhat other people might think, I suggest\nyou put that energy into enjoying yourself.
Yeah, I... I suppose you're right.
So! What say we start by hitting the\nfood stands?
No kidding. What the heck is drawing this\nmany people? Looks like...
'Preciate your custom!\nEat it while it's hot, ya hear?
Is that Natalie? Leave it to a professional\nto roll out a killer stall, I guess.
What do you think, Lathna?\nShould we get in line?
N-no thanks. I'm not big on crowds.
Guess we can always come back\nafter we do the rounds. Okay, then...\nFirst stop, that stall there!

Woof, I am beyond full. I swear they put
some kinda secret sauce in this stuff.
Same food at home? Meh. From a stall?
GOURMET. You enjoy yours, Lathna?
Yes. It was very tasty.\nI couldn't eat another bite.
Glad to hear it. If we want to catch the\npyroblossom show, we should probably\nmosey that way now.
Um, Curran? You...go on ahead.\nI need to make a quick stop first.
I know the way. Don't worry.\nGo on—I'll meet you at the show!
Ah! The pyroblossoms are starting.\nI need to hurry.
Oh, gosh, I'm the one who went\nbarrelling into you! Are you okay?
Phew. Good to hear.\nAnyway, I've gotta run. Bye!
Hm? Oh... This isn't my purse. That girl\nand I must've swapped ours on accident.
I've got to find her. But I need to meet\nup with Curran, too. Wh-what should I do?
No kidding. What a show! I'd say it was\nworth calling in a specialist from Taiwu.
Yeah... S-so, um... Where to next?
We gotta find your purse. I'm guessing\nit got mixed up with someone else's?
What?! H-how did you—\nI didn't say anything about that.
Sharp eyes are a tool of the trade.\nDoesn't take a purse scientist to see\nyou're packing a pristine pouch there.

Pray proffer a prospectus of—holy moly,
somebody get me off this alliteration train.
*ahem* Fill me in on what happened and
we'll take it from there.
—And then I met up with you\nfor the pyroblossom show.
It's going to be impossible to find the\nright girl in a crowd like this, though, so—
Eh, ＂impossible＂ is an awfully strong word.
Well? See her anywhere around \nthat stand?
Ah! There she is! That's her!
How'd you know where to look?
Easy. When you were running towards\nthe pyroblossom show, she was charging\nheadlong in the opposite direction.
That show's the festival's main attraction.\nErgo, she'd only ignore it if she wanted to\ndo something ELSE at precisely that time.
Something that couldn't wait until\nafter the show was over, for instance.
So, what's a girl to do while everyone\nelse is off watching the pyroblossoms?\nMy first thought: hit up the hottest stands.
I figured if we did the rounds on all the\nmost popular ones, we might find her.\nAaand bingo.
Whoa... You sound just like Heinwald.
Ugh. That guy's name is like a magic\nspell for ruining the moment.
Anyway, forget ol' skunk-hair. Go flag her\ndown and swap your bags back.
Huh? What's that about a purse?\nWhoa, you're right! This one isn't mine.
So they got switched when we bumped\ninto each other, huh? That could've ended\nbadly. Well, thanks for bringing it back!
And they lived happily ever after.\nThat, Lathna, is what we call an\n＂open-and-shut case.＂
It's the wrong one, Curran.\nThis isn't my purse!
